The paper deals with prediction algorithms and their performance in terms of loss and regret. This is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the tradeoff between loss and regret. The use of algorithms and their performance on input sequences suggests the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of experts and their performance, which falls under the category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the performance of the algorithm, which falls under the category of "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC).
